    "abstract": "<jats:title>ABSTRACT</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>\n                  \u00df-d-N4-hydroxycytidine (NHC), the parent nucleoside of molnupiravir, a COVID-19 antiviral, was quantified at sites of SARS-CoV-2 transmission in twelve patients enrolled in AGILE CST-2 (\n                  <jats:ext-link xmlns:xlink=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\" ext-link-type=\"clintrialgov\" xlink:href=\"NCT04746183\">NCT04746183</jats:ext-link>\n                  ). Saliva, nasal and tear concentrations were 3, 21 and 22% that of plasma. Saliva and nasal NHC concentrations were significantly correlated with plasma (\n                  <jats:italic>p</jats:italic>\n                  &lt;0.0001).\n                </jats:p>",
    "DOI": "10.1101/2021.12.06.21267342",
